\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\sa200\f3\fs22\f3\fs22\f3\fs22\lang1025\sl360\slmult1\qj 50.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\sl360\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls0\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\sa200\rtlch\af3\afs22\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe255\hich\f3\fs22\lang1033\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f3\fs22\lang1033\i0\b0\rtlch\ltrch\hich\f2\loch\f2 The general principle in our law is that courts do not impose costs on persons who are not party to a suit.  The policy underlying this principle is self-evident.  If a court for example mulcted witnesses with costs incurred by parties to a suit, no witnes
